07 Jul 2010 14:48






Actually, in many ways it's the polar opposite of Fred.

Think about it:

.

Bundle is reactive (he does what others say he does). Fred is active (free will).

Bundle comes out of stories. Fred goes into them.

Bundle only exists when written about by others. Fred writes himself into stories.

Fred alters the works of fiction he goes into. Bundle alters the reality he goes into.

Fred makes himself fictional. Bundle makes himself non-fictional.

Fred is harmless. Bundle is anything but.

.

These are not small differences. And what are the similarities, exactly?







